# Thorbis Theme Guidelines

## 🎨 THORBIS DESIGN SYSTEM

**ALL COMPONENTS MUST FOLLOW THE THORBIS THEME: Clean Black, White, Blue, and Neutral Colors**

### Core Theme Philosophy
- **Minimalist Design**: Clean, professional, and modern
- **High Contrast**: Excellent readability and accessibility
- **Brand Consistency**: Thorbis blue (#3B82F6) as primary accent
- **Neutral Foundation**: Black, white, and gray scale for content
- **No Gradients**: Flat, solid colors only
- **Dark Mode First**: Default to dark mode for modern UX

## 🎯 Color Palette

### Primary Colors
```css
/* Thorbis Blue - Primary Brand Color */
--primary: 217 91% 60%; /* #3B82F6 */
--primary-foreground: 0 0% 100%; /* White text on blue */

/* Neutral Grays - Content Foundation */
--background: 0 0% 0%; /* Pure black (dark mode) */
--foreground: 0 0% 100%; /* Pure white (dark mode) */
--card: 0 0% 4%; /* Very dark neutral */
--card-foreground: 0 0% 100%; /* Pure white */
```

### Secondary Colors
```css
/* Secondary and Accent Colors */
--secondary: 0 0% 8%; /* Dark neutral gray */
--secondary-foreground: 0 0% 100%; /* White text */
--accent: 217 91% 60%; /* Thorbis blue accent */
--accent-foreground: 0 0% 100%; /* White text on blue */

/* Muted and Border Colors */
--muted: 0 0% 8%; /* Dark neutral gray */
--muted-foreground: 0 0% 65%; /* Light neutral gray */
--border: 0 0% 12%; /* Medium dark neutral border */
--input: 0 0% 8%; /* Dark neutral input */
```

### Semantic Colors
```css
/* Success States - Subtle Green */
--success: 160 84% 39%; /* #10B981 - Success Green */
--success-foreground: 0 0% 100%; /* White text on green */

/* Error States - Muted Red */
--destructive: 0 84% 60%; /* #EF4444 - Error Red */
--destructive-foreground: 0 0% 100%; /* White text on red */

/* Warning States - Soft Orange */
--warning: 38 92% 50%; /* #F59E0B - Warning Orange */
--warning-foreground: 0 0% 0%; /* Black text on orange */
```

## 🚨 CRITICAL: NEVER USE THESE COLORS

### Forbidden Colors
- ❌ **Purple/Pink**: No purple or pink accents
- ❌ **Gradients**: No gradient backgrounds or text
- ❌ **Rainbow Colors**: No multi-color schemes
- ❌ **Overly Bright Colors**: No neon or overly saturated colors
- ❌ **Brand Colors**: No social media brand colors (Facebook blue, Twitter blue, etc.)

### Allowed Colors - Minimalist & Semantic
- ✅ **Thorbis Blue**: #3B82F6 (primary brand color)
- ✅ **Pure Black**: #000000 (backgrounds)
- ✅ **Pure White**: #FFFFFF (text and highlights)
- ✅ **Neutral Grays**: Various shades for content hierarchy
- ✅ **Success Green**: Subtle green for success states (#10B981)
- ✅ **Error Red**: Muted red for error states (#EF4444)
- ✅ **Warning Orange**: Soft orange for warnings (#F59E0B)
- ✅ **Transparency**: For overlays and effects

## 📋 Implementation Guidelines

### CSS Variables Usage
```css
/* ✅ CORRECT: Use CSS variables */
background-color: hsl(var(--background));
color: hsl(var(--foreground));
border-color: hsl(var(--border));

/* ❌ WRONG: Hard-coded colors */
background-color: #121212;
color: #EAEAEA;
border-color: #374151;
```

### Tailwind Classes
```jsx
// ✅ CORRECT: Use semantic Tailwind classes
<div className="bg-background text-foreground border-border">
<div className="bg-primary text-primary-foreground">
<div className="bg-muted text-muted-foreground">

// ❌ WRONG: Hard-coded color classes
<div className="bg-[#121212] text-[#EAEAEA]">
<div className="bg-gray-800 text-gray-200">
```

### Component Styling
```jsx
// ✅ CORRECT: Use theme-aware components
<Card className="bg-card text-card-foreground">
<Button className="bg-primary text-primary-foreground">
<Badge className="bg-muted text-muted-foreground">

// ❌ WRONG: Custom color styling
<Card className="bg-[#0a0a0a] text-[#EAEAEA]">
<Button className="bg-blue-500 text-white">
```

## ✍️ Typography System (Consistent Fonts & Sizes)

### Typeface
- **Primary (UI/Body/Headings)**: Inter, system-ui fallback
- **Monospace (Code/Numbers)**: SFMono-Regular/Monaco fallback

### Tailwind Font Families
```js
// tailwind.config.js (extend)
fontFamily: {
  sans: ["Inter", "ui-sans-serif", "system-ui", "Segoe UI", "Roboto", "Helvetica Neue", "Arial", "Noto Sans", "Apple Color Emoji", "Segoe UI Emoji", "Segoe UI Symbol"],
  mono: ["ui-monospace", "SFMono-Regular", "Menlo", "Monaco", "Consolas", "Liberation Mono", "Courier New"],
}
```

### Type Scale (Tailwind `fontSize`)
```text
- xs: 12/16 (labels, meta)
- sm: 14/20 (secondary text)
- base: 16/24 (body default)
- lg: 18/28 (section intro)
- xl: 20/28 (subhead)
- 2xl: 24/32 (H4)
- 3xl: 30/36 (H3)
- 4xl: 36/40 (H2)
- 5xl: 48/48 (H1 small)
- 6xl+: Hero tiers (sparingly)
```

### Usage Rules
- Headings: `text-foreground font-semibold` (avoid extra weights)
- Body: `text-muted-foreground` for secondary, `text-foreground` for primary
- Links: `text-primary` with `hover:underline` (no custom blues)
- Truncation: prefer `line-clamp-*` over manual clipping

## 📐 Spacing & Layout (Consistent Rhythm)

### Spacing Scale (Tailwind defaults, 4px base)
- Use multiples of 4: 4, 8, 12, 16, 20, 24, 32, 40, 48, 64
- Default section padding: `py-12 md:py-16`
- Default card padding: `p-4 md:p-6`
- Default grid gap: `gap-4 md:gap-6`

### Do/Don't
- Do use `space-y-*`/`space-x-*` for vertical rhythm
- Do maintain consistent gaps across similar components
- Don't mix arbitrary pixel paddings for similar components

## 🧱 Containers (Max Widths & Gutters)

### Container Rules
- Centered container with responsive gutters
- Max widths: `sm:640 md:768 lg:1024 xl:1280 2xl:1400`
- Gutters: `sm:1rem, md:1.5rem, lg+:2rem`

### Tailwind Container Config
```js
container: {
  center: true,
  padding: { DEFAULT: "1.5rem", sm: "1rem", md: "1.5rem", lg: "2rem", xl: "2rem", "2xl": "2rem" },
  screens: { sm: "640px", md: "768px", lg: "1024px", xl: "1280px", "2xl": "1400px" }
}
```

### Usage
- Page shells: `container` on top-level wrappers
- Avoid nested `container` inside `container`
- Use `max-w-*` on feature blocks when needed (e.g., `max-w-3xl` for article)

## 🧩 Component Layout Patterns

- Card: `bg-card text-card-foreground border border-border rounded-lg p-4 md:p-6`
- Section: `py-12 md:py-16 border-b border-border/30`
- Toolbar: `h-10 px-3 md:px-4 rounded-md bg-secondary text-secondary-foreground`

## 🧾 Typography Plugin Defaults

Tailwind Typography is configured to use theme colors. Prefer prose classes for content-rich blocks:
```jsx
<article className="prose prose-invert">
  {/* markdown/content */}
</article>
```

## 🎨 Design Patterns

### Text Hierarchy
```jsx
// Primary headings
<h1 className="text-foreground font-bold text-4xl">

// Secondary headings  
<h2 className="text-foreground font-semibold text-2xl">

// Body text
<p className="text-foreground">

// Muted text
<span className="text-muted-foreground">
```

### Interactive Elements
```jsx
// Primary buttons
<Button className="bg-primary text-primary-foreground hover:bg-primary/90">

// Secondary buttons
<Button variant="secondary" className="bg-secondary text-secondary-foreground">

// Destructive actions
<Button variant="destructive" className="bg-destructive text-destructive-foreground">
```

### Cards and Containers
```jsx
// Main content cards
<Card className="bg-card text-card-foreground border-border">

// Muted containers
<div className="bg-muted text-muted-foreground p-4 rounded-lg">

// Accent highlights
<div className="bg-accent/10 text-accent-foreground border border-accent/20">
```

## 🔧 Migration Checklist

### Files to Update
1. **Business Profile Pages**: Remove hard-coded dark colors
2. **Authentication Components**: Update social media icons to neutral colors
3. **Dashboard Components**: Ensure consistent theming
4. **Landing Pages**: Update any custom color schemes
5. **Form Components**: Use theme variables for all styling

### Common Replacements
```jsx
// Replace hard-coded colors with theme variables
"#121212" → "hsl(var(--background))"
"#EAEAEA" → "hsl(var(--foreground))"
"#0a0a0a" → "hsl(var(--card))"
"#374151" → "hsl(var(--border))"
"#6B7280" → "hsl(var(--muted-foreground))"

// Replace Tailwind color classes
"bg-gray-800" → "bg-card"
"text-gray-200" → "text-card-foreground"
"border-gray-700" → "border-border"
```

## 🚨 Enforcement Rules

### Always Do:
- Use CSS variables for all colors
- Follow the Thorbis blue + neutral color scheme
- Implement dark mode by default
- Use semantic color names
- Test contrast ratios for accessibility

### Never Do:
- Use hard-coded hex colors
- Implement rainbow or multi-color schemes
- Use gradients or complex color patterns
- Ignore the established color palette
- Create custom color variations

### Code Review Checklist:
- [ ] No hard-coded hex colors
- [ ] Uses CSS variables for theming
- [ ] Follows Thorbis blue + neutral scheme
- [ ] Implements proper dark mode support
- [ ] Maintains accessibility standards
- [ ] No gradients or complex patterns

## 🎯 Success Metrics

### Visual Consistency:
- **100%** of components use theme variables
- **0** hard-coded color values
- **Consistent** brand recognition across all pages
- **Professional** and modern appearance

### Accessibility:
- **WCAG AA** contrast compliance
- **High contrast** for all text elements
- **Clear visual hierarchy** using neutral grays
- **Consistent** focus indicators

**Remember: The Thorbis theme is about simplicity, professionalism, and consistency. Every color choice should reinforce the brand identity.**
